{
  "text": "In our recent paper [CITATION_1] , we described an approach called green scheduling to reduce the peak demand of a large number of heating systems. We proposed a more general constraint that at most k \u2265 1 actuators can be activated at any time. The system model considered in the paper was affine dynamics with no interaction between the sub-systems and no disturbances. The main contribution of this paper is twofold.",
  "citation_candidates": [
